Democratic Alliance MP Natasha Mazzone has suggested that members of the Gupta family also be called to answer questions. CAPE TOWN - Members of Parliament have agreed that an inquiry into Eskom would also include a probe into allegations of state capture involving the controversial Gupta family.Parliament's portfolio committee on public enterprises on Wednesday adopted the terms of reference of the inquiry.The parliamentary investigation was prompted by the sudden reappointment of Brian Molefe as Eskom s chief executive officer, just months after he had left the utility.Minister Lynne Brown has since ordered the utility's board to rescind Molefe's appointment.Zukiswa Rantho, the portfolio committee's acting chairperson, says allegations of state capture related to Eskom will be investigated. It will also go to the issues of the emails, and also the contracts, the coal contracts. Democratic Alliance MP Natasha Mazzone has suggested that members of the Gupta family also be called to answer questions. If we are to get to the bottom of this, we need every single one of the role players present, and that includes Atul Gupta, Ajay Gupta, and most certainly Duduzane Zuma. Leaked emails have exposed the Gupta family's network of influence over government.MPs are hoping to get their hands on some of the emails relevant to their inquiry, which is expected to begin in August.(Edited by Zinhle Nkosi)